Building SAMRAI using CMake:

    mkdir build && cd build
    cmake ../
    make

Third-party libraries will be detected by CMake based on what is in your path.
On LC systems, the `use` command should set the right environment variables.
Alternatively, you can use `CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH` to point CMake at the locations
of the libraries. The only required library is boost. HDF5 is enabled by
default but can be turned off by passing the argument `-DENABLE_HDF5=Off` to
CMake.  More extensive instructions on building and installing SAMRAI using
CMake are available in the INSTALL-NOTES file.


Building SAMRAI with Proteus (MI300A / HIP):

  A self-contained build script is provided for building SAMRAI with GPU
  support on MI300A (gfx942) using ROCm, HIP, RAJA, Umpire, and the Proteus
  JIT compiler. The script downloads and builds all TPL dependencies
  (CAMP, Umpire, Proteus, RAJA JIT branch) then builds SAMRAI itself.

  Prerequisites:
    - TOSS 4 (Cray) system with MI300A GPUs
    - ROCm 6.4.0 (rocmcc compiler)
    - cray-mpich 8.1.31 (GPU-aware MPI)
    - CMake 3.29+

  Full build (TPLs + SAMRAI):

    ./build_samrai_mi300a.sh

  Build only TPL dependencies:

    ./build_samrai_mi300a.sh --tpl-only

  Rebuild only SAMRAI (after TPLs are already built):

    ./build_samrai_mi300a.sh --samrai-only

  The build produces:
    - TPL installs in tpl_build_mi300a/install/
    - SAMRAI build in build_mi300a/

  Key build options enabled:
    - ENABLE_HIP=On             GPU offloading via HIP
    - ENABLE_RAJA=On            RAJA portability layer
    - ENABLE_UMPIRE=On          Umpire memory management
    - RAJA_ENABLE_JIT=On        JIT compilation via Proteus
    - ENABLE_SAMRAI_DEVICE_ALLOC=On   MPI buffers stay on device (GPU-aware MPI)

  Runtime environment:
    - Set MPICH_GPU_SUPPORT_ENABLED=1 before running
    - LD_LIBRARY_PATH may need /usr/tce/packages/cce/cce-17.0.0-magic/cce/x86_64/lib
